Identification_Area.title: Cassini VIMS Image Index Table for the Cruise to Saturn

Citation_Information.author_list: M. R. Showalter, R. S. French, M. W. Evans, M. K. Gordon, and M. S. Tiscareno
Citation_Information.description: This table describes the general properties of each Cassini VIMS cube.

Modification_Detail.description: The "File Specification" column has been replaced by "File Name".

File.comment: This table describes the general properties of each Cassini VIMS cube.

Table_Character.description:
This Cassini VIMS image index has been adapted by the PDS Ring-Moon Systems Node for the PDS4 version of the data set. This file was obtained from the RMS Node website at this URL: https://pds-rings.seti.org/viewmaster/metadata/COVIMS_0xxx/COVIMS_0999/COVIMS_0999_index.tab It was downloaded on July 30, 2019. Two additional, leading columns, containing the image LID and PDS4 raw image file path, have been pre-pended to each record; the remainder of each record is unchanged.
For cases in which multiple versions of the same VIMS cube are provided in this bundle, metadata is only provided for the latest version.
Following is the description field of the file as originally downloaded.
This version of the Cassini VIMS image index has been edited by the PDS Ring-Moon Systems Node for compliance with PDS3 standards. Invalid rows have been edited so they obey the specified DATA_TYPE and can therefore be read more easily by software. For example, where a numeric column contained '*****', that value has been replaced by '-1.E32' and, in the label, a numeric value of -1.E32 has been identified as the NULL_CONSTANT or NOT_APPLICABLE_CONSTANT.
In addition, PDS3 syntax errors have been corrected in this label.
Note that NULL_CONSTANT identifies values that could be known but are not, whereas NOT_APPLICABLE_CONSTANT refers to values that are undefined. An example of the former would be a missing value of SC_SUN_POSITION_VECTOR; an example of the latter would be a value of LOWER_LEFT_LATITUDE in an image where the lower left corner does not intercept the target body.

Field_Character.name: Image LID
Field_Character.description: The LID for this image cube.

Field_Character.name: File Name
Field_Character.description: The name of the associated raw data file.

Field_Character.name: PDS3_FILE_NAME
Field_Character.description: The PDS3 name of the associated raw data file.

Field_Character.name: PATH_NAME
Field_Character.description: POSIX-compliant full path to the PDS3 label file.

Field_Character.name: SEQ_ID
Field_Character.description: Sequence id: 1st character is either C or S indicating Cruise or Tour, respectively. 2nd-4th characters indicate sequence number

Field_Character.name: START_TIME
Field_Character.description: Spacecraft Event Time (SCET) of the VIMS IR shutter opening in the format YYYY-MM-DDThh:mm:ss.[fff], where YYYY is the year, MM is the month, DD is the day, hh is the hour, mm is the minutes, and ss.[fff] are the seconds.

Field_Character.name: STOP_TIME
Field_Character.description: Spacecraft Event Time (SCET) of the VIMS IR shutter closing in the format YYYY-MM-DDThh:mm:ss.[fff], where YYYY is the year, MM is the month, DD is the day, hh is the hour, mm is the minutes, and ss.[fff] are the seconds.

Field_Character.name: SPACECRAFT_CLOCK_START_COUNT
Field_Character.description: Spacecraft clock start count reading of the VIMS IR shutter opening.

Field_Character.name: SPACECRAFT_CLOCK_STOP_COUNT
Field_Character.description: Spacecraft clock stop count reading of the VIMS IR shutter closing.

Field_Character.name: TARGET_NAME
Field_Character.description: The target name identifies the primary target of the observation.

Field_Character.name: INSTRUMENT_MODE_ID
Field_Character.description: The mode in which the instrument is acquiring data, most commonly IMAGE but also LINE, POINT, OCCULTATION, CAL_SOLAR, CAL_SPECTRAL, CAL_BACKGROUND, or CAL_ELECTRIC.

Field_Character.name: OBSERVATION_ID
Field_Character.description: A string that consists of the instrument, the orbit number, the target code, a description of the observation, and instance number. For example, VIMS_000PH_PHOEBE031 is data of PHOEBE taken by VIMS during orbit 000.

Field_Character.name: SPECTRAL_EDITING
Field_Character.description: Indicates whether this cube has been reduced to a subset of the bands in the original cube. If 'OFF', none of the original bands of the cube were intentionally omitted. See BAND_BIN_ORIGINAL_BAND to determine which bands are present.

Field_Character.name: SPECTRAL_SUMMING
Field_Character.description: Indicates whether this cube has had some bands summed to reduce the SSR data volume. See BAND_BIN_ORIGINAL_BAND to determine which bands have been summed.

Field_Character.name: STAR_TRACKING
Field_Character.description: Normally, the VIMS field of view is changed by altering the size (SWATH_WIDTH and SWATH_LENGTH) of the subset of the array and by changing the position of that subset (X_OFFSET and Z_OFFSET) within the array. This is the default, when STAR_TRACKING is OFF. When STAR_TRACKING is ON, the tracking is accomplished by causing the instrument to ignore the supplied X and Z offsets in the instrument setup, and instead track the brightest pixel in the array as it moves over time. The brightest pixel is set in the instrument by running a previous instrument setup (of a minimal size), which will cause the X and Z position of the brightest pixel to be automatically set inside the instrument. This position is then used as the initial brightest pixel, and it will be tracked over the life of this setup.

Field_Character.name: SWATH_WIDTH
Field_Character.description: The number of pixels (in the X direction) collected during an observation. This will differ from CORE_ITEMS (1) for Occultation Mode cubes. The angular size of these pixels is dependent upon the resolution mode selected.

Field_Character.name: SWATH_LENGTH
Field_Character.description: The number of slices (in the Z direction) collected during an observation. This will differ from CORE_ITEMS (3) for all packed cubes and Occultation Mode cubes. The angular size of these lines is dependent upon the resolution mode selected.

Field_Character.name: IR_EXPOSURE
Field_Character.description: The IR exposure time for each pixel, in milliseconds.

Field_Character.name: IR_SAMPLING_MODE_ID
Field_Character.description: The spatial resolution mode of the IR channel. Either NORMAL for 0.5 mrad x 0.5 mrad pixels, or UNDER for NYQUIST sampling (0.5 x 0.5 mrad), or HI-RES for 0.25 x 0.50 mrad sampling.

Field_Character.name: VIS_EXPOSURE
Field_Character.description: The VIS exposure time for each line, in milliseconds.

Field_Character.name: VIS_SAMPLING_MODE_ID
Field_Character.description: The spatial resolution mode of the VIS channel. Either NORMAL for 0.5 mrad x 0.5 mrad pixels, or HI-RES sampling (0.167 x 0.167 mrad), or N/A if the VIS channel is OFF.

Field_Character.name: PRODUCT_ID
Field_Character.description: A permanent, unique identifier assigned to a data product by its producer. The product id is the sclk string that represents the spacecraft time at the moment that the data was taken. The SCLK string is a spacecraft timing partion (usually 1) followed by a forward slash followed by the spacecraft clock value (an integer representing the amount of time since the spacecraft partition became active. For example: 1/1356766628.

Field_Character.name: VOLUME_ID
Field_Character.description: Name of the volume id which the data cube resides.

Field_Character.name: CENTER_LATITUDE
Field_Character.description: Planetocentric latitude at aimpoint on target (or Ring_Aimpoint_Latitude if target is a ring).

Field_Character.name: CENTER_LONGITUDE
Field_Character.description: West longitude at aimpoint on target (or Ring_Aimpoint_Longitude if target is a ring).

Field_Character.name: CENTRAL_BODY_DISTANCE
Field_Character.description: Distance from the spacecraft to the center of primary body.

Field_Character.name: COORDINATE_SYSTEM_NAME
Field_Character.description: The full name of the coordinate system to which the state vectors are referenced.

Field_Character.name: DECLINATION
Field_Character.description: Declination of camera optic axis.

Field_Character.name: EMISSION_ANGLE
Field_Character.description: Emission angle at aimpoint on target.

Field_Character.name: INCIDENCE_ANGLE
Field_Character.description: Incidence angle at aimpoint on target.

Field_Character.name: LOWER_LEFT_LATITUDE
Field_Character.description: Planetocentric latitude of lower-left pixel.

Field_Character.name: LOWER_LEFT_LONGITUDE
Field_Character.description: West longitude of lower-left pixel.

Field_Character.name: LOWER_RIGHT_LATITUDE
Field_Character.description: Planetocentric latitude of lower-right pixel.

Field_Character.name: LOWER_RIGHT_LONGITUDE
Field_Character.description: West longitude of lower-right pixel.

Field_Character.name: MAXIMUM_RING_RADIUS
Field_Character.description: Maximum ringplane radius in image.

Field_Character.name: MINIMUM_RING_RADIUS
Field_Character.description: Maximum ringplane radius in image.

Field_Character.name: NORTH_AZIMUTH_CLOCK_ANGLE
Field_Character.description: Direction of the northward-pointing azimuth at at the aimpoint on the target body, measured clock-wise.

Field_Character.name: PHASE_ANGLE
Field_Character.description: Phase angle at sub spacecraft point on target.

Field_Character.name: PIXEL_SCALE
Field_Character.description: Size of one pixel at sub spacecraft point on target body.

Field_Character.name: PLANET_CENTER
Field_Character.description: 2-valued array. First, Line of target body center. Second, Sample of target body center.

Field_Character.name: RIGHT_ASCENSION
Field_Character.description: Right ascension of camera optic axis.

Field_Character.name: RING_EMISSION_ANGLE
Field_Character.description: Emission angle relative to target ring northward- pointing normal at aimpoint.

Field_Character.name: RING_INCIDENCE_ANGLE
Field_Character.description: Incidence angle relative to target ring northward-pointing normal at aimpoint.

Field_Character.name: SC_PLANET_POSITION_VECTOR
Field_Character.description: 3-valued array. X,Y,Z components of the position vector from spacecraft to primary planet center, corrected for light-travel time and stellar aberration.

Field_Character.name: SC_PLANET_VELOCITY_VECTOR
Field_Character.description: 3-valued array. X,Y,Z components of the velocity vector of primary planet relative to spacecraft, corrected for light-travel time.

Field_Character.name: SC_SUN_POSITION_VECTOR
Field_Character.description: 3-valued array. X,Y,Z components of the position vector from spacecraft to sun center, corrected for light-travel time and stellar aberration.

Field_Character.name: SC_SUN_VELOCITY_VECTOR
Field_Character.description: 3-valued array. X,Y,Z components of the velocity vector of sun relative to spacecraft, corrected for light-travel time.

Field_Character.name: SC_TARGET_POSITION_VECTOR
Field_Character.description: 3-valued array. X,Y,Z components of the position vector from spacecraft to target center, corrected for light-travel time and stellar aberration.

Field_Character.name: SC_TARGET_VELOCITY_VECTOR
Field_Character.description: 3-valued array. X,Y,Z components of the velocity vector of the target relative to spacecraft, corrected for light-travel time.

Field_Character.name: SUB_SOLAR_LATITUDE
Field_Character.description: Planetocentric latitude of sub solar point on target; Ring_Subsolar_Latitude if target is a ring.

Field_Character.name: SUB_SOLAR_LONGITUDE
Field_Character.description: West longitude of sub solar point on target; Ring_Subsolar_Longitude if target is a ring.

Field_Character.name: SUB_SPACECRAFT_LATITUDE
Field_Character.description: Planetocentric latitude of sub spacecraft point on target; Ring_Subspacecraft_Latitude if target is a ring.

Field_Character.name: SUB_SPACECRAFT_LONGITUDE
Field_Character.description: West longitude of sub spacecraft point on target; Ring_Subsolar_Longitude if target is a ring.

Field_Character.name: TARGET_DISTANCE
Field_Character.description: Distance from the spacecraft to the center of the target.

Field_Character.name: TARGET_EASTERNMOST_LONGITUDE
Field_Character.description: Easternmost longitude visible on target body.

Field_Character.name: TARGET_NORTHERNMOST_LATITUDE
Field_Character.description: Northernmost latitude visible on target body.

Field_Character.name: TARGET_SOUTHERNMOST_LATITUDE
Field_Character.description: Southernmost latitude visible on target body.

Field_Character.name: TARGET_WESTERNMOST_LONGITUDE
Field_Character.description: Westernmost latitude visible on target body.

Field_Character.name: TWIST_ANGLE
Field_Character.description: Twist angle of optic axis.

Field_Character.name: UPPER_LEFT_LATITUDE
Field_Character.description: Planetocentric latitude of upper-left pixel.

Field_Character.name: UPPER_LEFT_LONGITUDE
Field_Character.description: West longitude of upper-left pixel.

Field_Character.name: UPPER_RIGHT_LATITUDE
Field_Character.description: Planetocentric latitude of upper-right pixel.

Field_Character.name: UPPER_RIGHT_LONGITUDE
Field_Character.description: West longitude of upper-right pixel.
